# cron.example — schwab-positions-mcp token-health probe scheduling

Schwab refresh tokens expire after a **hard, non-extendable 7 days**. There
is no fully-automatic keep-alive (using the refresh token does NOT reset the
7-day clock — the window runs from the token's original creation). The next
best thing is a scheduled health probe that warns you *before* the token dies
so re-authorizing is predictable instead of surprising.

This file shows how to schedule `python -m schwab_positions_mcp.health` on
each OS. Customize the path substitutions (`uv` path, repo path) for your
machine. The probe:

- exits `0` healthy / `1` <24h / `2` <12h-or-expired / `3` missing /
  `4` malformed / `5` insecure perms,
- fires a desktop notification + writes
  `~/Desktop/SCHWAB_POSITIONS_REAUTH_NEEDED.md` on any non-zero exit,
- never opens a browser and never touches Schwab state (offline-safe).

The schedule below biases toward typical "at the keyboard" windows (weekend
evening + mid-week evening) plus a 4-hour fallback for laptops that were
asleep during a scheduled run.

---

## macOS (launchd)

Save as
`~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.kevinkda.schwab-positions-mcp.health.plist`,
then load with:

```bash
launchctl load -w ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.kevinkda.schwab-positions-mcp.health.plist
```

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>com.kevinkda.schwab-positions-mcp.health</string>

    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
        <string>/Users/YOURUSER/.local/bin/uv</string>
        <string>--directory</string>
        <string>/Users/YOURUSER/code/kevinkda/schwab-positions-mcp</string>
        <string>run</string>
        <string>python</string>
        <string>-m</string>
        <string>schwab_positions_mcp.health</string>
    </array>

    <!-- Primary cadence: Sunday 20:00 + Wednesday 21:00 (24h clock). -->
    <key>StartCalendarInterval</key>
    <array>
        <dict>
            <key>Weekday</key><integer>0</integer>  <!-- Sunday -->
            <key>Hour</key><integer>20</integer>
            <key>Minute</key><integer>0</integer>
        </dict>
        <dict>
            <key>Weekday</key><integer>3</integer>  <!-- Wednesday -->
            <key>Hour</key><integer>21</integer>
            <key>Minute</key><integer>0</integer>
        </dict>
    </array>

    <!-- Lid-close fallback: launchd misses StartCalendarInterval while the
         laptop is sleeping and DOES NOT auto-catch-up. StartInterval=14400
         (4h) ensures we re-probe shortly after wake. -->
    <key>StartInterval</key>
    <integer>14400</integer>

    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>

    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>/Users/YOURUSER/.local/state/schwab-positions-mcp/health.out.log</string>
    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>/Users/YOURUSER/.local/state/schwab-positions-mcp/health.err.log</string>
</dict>
</plist>
```

> Replace `YOURUSER` with the output of `whoami`. If you use mise / pyenv,
> point `ProgramArguments[0]` at the absolute path returned by `which uv`.

---

## Linux (crontab)

Append to `crontab -e`:

```cron
# schwab-positions-mcp token health probe — primary slots (24h clock).
MAILTO=""   # leave empty unless you have sendmail / msmtp configured.
0 20 * * 0 cd "$HOME/code/kevinkda/schwab-positions-mcp" && "$HOME/.local/bin/uv" run python -m schwab_positions_mcp.health >> "$HOME/.local/state/schwab-positions-mcp/health.out.log" 2>> "$HOME/.local/state/schwab-positions-mcp/health.err.log"
0 21 * * 3 cd "$HOME/code/kevinkda/schwab-positions-mcp" && "$HOME/.local/bin/uv" run python -m schwab_positions_mcp.health >> "$HOME/.local/state/schwab-positions-mcp/health.out.log" 2>> "$HOME/.local/state/schwab-positions-mcp/health.err.log"

# 4h fall-back so we still notice <12h-to-expiry on a workday.
0 */4 * * * cd "$HOME/code/kevinkda/schwab-positions-mcp" && "$HOME/.local/bin/uv" run python -m schwab_positions_mcp.health >> "$HOME/.local/state/schwab-positions-mcp/health.out.log" 2>> "$HOME/.local/state/schwab-positions-mcp/health.err.log"
```

If you have `sendmail` / `msmtp` installed, set `MAILTO=you@example.com` —
cron will email the script's stderr whenever the probe exits with code 2
(critical).

---

## Windows native (Task Scheduler) — experimental

Save the following as `register-schwab-positions-health.ps1` and run **once**
in an elevated PowerShell:

```powershell
$Repo   = "$env:USERPROFILE\code\kevinkda\schwab-positions-mcp"
$UvBin  = "$env:USERPROFILE\.local\bin\uv.exe"
$LogDir = "$env:LOCALAPPDATA\schwab-positions-mcp"
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path $LogDir | Out-Null

$Action = New-ScheduledTaskAction `
    -Execute $UvBin `
    -Argument "--directory `"$Repo`" run python -m schwab_positions_mcp.health" `
    -WorkingDirectory $Repo

# Sunday 20:00 + Wednesday 21:00 + every 4 hours fallback.
$Triggers = @(
    (New-ScheduledTaskTrigger -Weekly -DaysOfWeek Sunday    -At 8:00PM),
    (New-ScheduledTaskTrigger -Weekly -DaysOfWeek Wednesday -At 9:00PM),
    (New-ScheduledTaskTrigger -Once -At (Get-Date) -RepetitionInterval (New-TimeSpan -Hours 4))
)

$Principal = New-ScheduledTaskPrincipal -UserId "$env:USERNAME" -LogonType Interactive
$Settings  = New-ScheduledTaskSettingsSet `
    -StartWhenAvailable `
    -DontStopOnIdleEnd `
    -ExecutionTimeLimit (New-TimeSpan -Minutes 5)

Register-ScheduledTask `
    -TaskName "SchwabPositionsMcpHealth" `
    -Action $Action `
    -Trigger $Triggers `
    -Principal $Principal `
    -Settings $Settings `
    -Description "schwab-positions-mcp token-health probe (read-only)."
```

To remove later:

```powershell
Unregister-ScheduledTask -TaskName "SchwabPositionsMcpHealth" -Confirm:$false
```

---

## Verifying the schedule

```bash
# Run the probe now (exit code reflects token state).
uv run python -m schwab_positions_mcp.health
echo "exit code: $?"

# Inspect the structured JSON log line.
tail -1 "$HOME/.local/state/schwab-positions-mcp/health.err.log"
```

When the token is within 24h of expiry (or already expired), you will get a
desktop notification and a `~/Desktop/SCHWAB_POSITIONS_REAUTH_NEEDED.md` file
containing the one-command fix:

```bash
uv run python -m schwab_positions_mcp.auth login_flow
```

Your App Key / Secret stay in `.env`, so re-authorizing is just the browser
login — you never re-register the app.
